item.title: Groovy Digs VIII
item.description:
Groovy Digs VIII


Ah, the siren call of Twin Cities living. How silly. A house in the Prospect Park neighborhood of Minneapolis, a quiet little neighborhood that isn't really on the way to anywhere or have anything to attract people to (save The Witches Tower which opens to the public once a year). It's close to the U, close to bicycle and walking paths, close to 94 and 280, and close to decent public transit...all in all 172 Bedford St SE, Minneapolis MN 55414 is a groovy 3 bed, 1.5 bath, 1,368 sq ft house with a cute little alley and a two car garage.

- April Witteveen, CROOK COUNTY LIBRARY: It has been a pleasure to serve you

item.title: Andrew Hartzler
item.description:
Andrew Hartzler


You want the power to force your religious beliefs onto everyone else and because you don't have that power you feel like you're being silenced, but you're not. You're just gonna have to learn to coexist with all of us and I'm sure it's not that hard.

- Andrew Hartzler to Aunt Vicky, Rep. Vicky Hartzler who spoke against the Respect for Marriage Act
